race.comment: The penny has dropped for MR BUSTER (4) who has put back-to-back wins together and is racing with a lot of confidence this preparation. Is one from one over this track and trip and should be right there when the whips are cracking. COUNTER (6) returned to the winners' stall at Eagle Farm last time out and winning rider Jones stays on top. Should give a bold sight again. CONNECTICUT (3) goes well for hoop Bayliss who has two wins and five placings from just nine steers. Usually thereabouts and must be included in calculations. NIKAU SPUR (1) has only missed a drum once in five attempts over this ten-furlong test and gets some weight relief with the 3kg claim. Top-three credentials. TAPILDOODLEDO (2) next in line.
